description:
&lt;p&gt;We require a highly motivated and enthusiastic person to join our weekend staff team on a temporary basis until 31st March 2021, working alternate weekends 8.00 am – 5.00 pm. The post will include working Bank Holidays as per the weekend shift rota and will also include covering for sickness, annual leave, weekend evenings and maternity leave where necessary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Duties will include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Dealing with emergency admissions, transferring and discharging patients onto the PAS Computer System in response to telephone requests&lt;br /&gt;• Locating and retrieving and preparing case notes for emergency admissions&lt;br /&gt;• Re-filing medical case notes into store&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The following will be essential:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• The ability to lift and carry heavy medical case notes and cope with a lot of walking around the site&lt;br /&gt;• A good standard of education including GCSE English at Grade c or above&lt;br /&gt;• Excellent communication skills&lt;br /&gt;• Attention to detail and accurate input of data to the computer system&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous Patient Administration experience is preferred together with good computer skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Shirley Timson Cordinator Case Note Store/Clinic Prep Email address Shirley.Timson@nhs.net Tel: 2517&lt;/p&gt;
